# Handled Home — Add-on Specs: Category Requirements Matrix + Opportunity Banner Decision Tree (v1)

This document adds:
1) A **field-by-field required/optional matrix** per category (California launch, v1)
2) A deterministic **opportunity banner decision tree** (when multiple categories are selected)

---

# PART A — Category Requirements Matrix (CA v1)

## A0) Design philosophy (do this or onboarding will collapse)
- Only require what is needed for **safety, legality, payouts, and trust**.
- Treat most compliance as **ops-verified** initially.
- Use a config table to drive the UI dynamically.

### Core fields (always required for all providers)
**Identity / business**
- Legal name
- Phone
- Email
- Business type (sole prop / LLC / corp)
- Home base ZIP
- Service area ZIPs/zones
- Categories selected
- Availability (days/hours)
- Agreement clauses accepted
- Payout setup complete (Stripe Connect)

**Operational commitment**
- Proof-of-work acceptance
- No side payments acceptance
- SKU + Levels compliance acceptance

---

## A1) Category Risk Tiers (simplifies compliance logic)

### Tier 0 — Low risk / no license expected
Examples:
- Trash bin concierge
- Dog poop scoop / pet yard sanitation
- Basic exterior sweep / cobweb removal (if you offer)
- (Possibly) simple “yard waste pickup” if not using power tools

**Default required**
- General liability: recommended, not required at application (but can be required for activation)
- Background check: not required
- License: not required

### Tier 1 — Medium risk / insurance strongly recommended
Examples:
- Window cleaning (outside)
- Pressure washing
- Gutter cleaning (height risk)
- Yard cleanup / hauling

**Default required**
- General liability: REQUIRED (upload COI or enter carrier/policy; ops verifies)
- Background check: optional (enable for “premium” tier later)
- License: not required unless work crosses into regulated trade work

### Tier 2 — Higher risk / trade-adjacent / higher dispute potential
Examples:
- Lawn mowing/landscaping (power tools, property damage risk)
- Regular house cleaning (in-home access, trust/safety risk)
- Handyman “fix list” (scope creep + potential regulated work)

**Default required**
- General liability: REQUIRED
- Workers comp: REQUIRED if employees (attestation + COI)
- Background check: REQUIRED for any in-home category (cleaning/handyman) in v1 if you want premium trust
- License: “may be required depending on scope” → ops review gating

### Tier 3 — Licensed contractor likely required (regulated)
Examples (depending on scope):
- Certain handyman tasks beyond minor repairs
- Trades that clearly require CSLB license (electrical/plumbing/HVAC/etc.)

**Default required**
- CSLB license number: REQUIRED
- General liability: REQUIRED
- Workers comp if employees: REQUIRED
- Background check: REQUIRED
- Ops review only (no auto-approval)

